rComments: It's true that he says he didn't study Art History. He also says he doesn't go to galleries.

He says that he's never taken an Art History course and that he does not know anything about this subject. This means that he should not be the Chair of the Department. He should teach and supervise students in the Department of Anthropology, which hosts his field, Archaeology.

I love him as a person and the class seems like an amazing topic to teach however I can't deny i did leave his lectures feeling uninformed and confused; probably because although the subject of the Aegean Bronze Age is interesting it is difficult to teach. So you can do it if you really try, just be prepared to do so.

He was very clear, interesting, funny, organized and kept you motivated to keep working. It also helps that he has a British Accent and would always try to find the "Canadian" version of the British joke/expression he was using. Would definitely take his class again!
